The paper discusses a theoretical framework for evaluating the retrieval effectiveness of search engines, with a focus on search engines that present enriched results. This topic falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper discusses the design of retrieval effectiveness tests, which is relevant to Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The use of machine learning and natural language processing techniques to improve search engines is also mentioned, which relates to Deep Learning (cs.DL) and Databases (cs.DB).
